#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.55"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.55:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.55:0.2"
msgid "6. Sacittavagga"
msgstr "6. Your Own Mind"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.55:0.3"
msgid "55. Parihānasutta"
msgstr "55. Decline"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an10.55:1.1"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:"

#. VAR: bhikkhave”ti → bhikkhavoti (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an10.55:1.2"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an10.55:1.3"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "an10.55:1.4"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr "Sāriputta said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.103"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an10.55:2.1"
msgid "“‘Parihānadhammo puggalo, parihānadhammo puggalo’ti, āvuso, vuccati."
msgstr "“Reverends, they speak of a person liable to decline,"

msgctxt "an10.55:2.2"
msgid "‘Aparihānadhammo puggalo, aparihānadhammo puggalo’ti, āvuso, vuccati."
msgstr "and one not liable to decline."

msgctxt "an10.55:2.3"
msgid ""
"Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, parihānadhammo puggalo vutto bhagavatā, kittāvatā "
"ca pana aparihānadhammo puggalo vutto bhagavatā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"But how did the Buddha define a person liable to decline, and one not liable "
"to decline?”"

msgctxt "an10.55:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Dūratopi kho mayaṃ, āvuso, āgacchāma āyasmato sāriputtassa santike etassa "
"bhāsitassa atthamaññātuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend, we would travel a long way to learn the meaning of this statement "
"in the presence of Venerable Sāriputta."

msgctxt "an10.55:2.5"
msgid "Sādhu vatāyasmantaṃyeva sāriputtaṃ paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho."
msgstr "May Venerable Sāriputta himself please clarify the meaning of this."

msgctxt "an10.55:2.6"
msgid "Āyasmato sāriputtassa sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr "The mendicants will listen and remember it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an10.55:3.1"
msgid "“Tenahāvuso, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Then listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "an10.55:3.2"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "an10.55:3.3"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr "Sāriputta said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an10.55:4.1"
msgid "“Kittāvatā nu kho, āvuso, parihānadhammo puggalo vutto bhagavatā?"
msgstr "“How did the Buddha define a person liable to decline?"

msgctxt "an10.55:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu assutañceva dhammaṃ na suṇāti, sutā cassa dhammā sammosaṃ "
"gacchanti, ye cassa dhammā pubbe cetaso asamphuṭṭhapubbā te cassa na "
"samudācaranti, aviññātañceva na vijānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t get to hear a teaching they haven’t heard "
"before. They forget those teachings they have heard. They don’t keep "
"rehearsing the teachings they’ve already got to know. And they don’t come to "
"understand what they haven’t understood before."

msgctxt "an10.55:4.3"
msgid "Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, parihānadhammo puggalo vutto bhagavatā."
msgstr "That’s how the Buddha defined a person liable to decline."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an10.55:5.1"
msgid "Kittāvatā ca panāvuso, aparihānadhammo puggalo vutto bhagavatā?"
msgstr "And how did the Buddha define a person not liable to decline?"

msgctxt "an10.55:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, bhikkhu assutañceva dhammaṃ suṇāti, sutā cassa dhammā na sammosaṃ "
"gacchanti, ye cassa dhammā pubbe cetaso asamphuṭṭhapubbā te cassa "
"samudācaranti, aviññātañceva vijānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant gets to hear a teaching they haven’t heard before. "
"They remember those teachings they have heard. They keep rehearsing the "
"teachings they’ve already got to know. And they come to understand what they "
"haven’t understood before."

msgctxt "an10.55:5.3"
msgid "Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, aparihānadhammo puggalo vutto bhagavatā."
msgstr "That’s how the Buddha defined a person not liable to decline."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an10.55:6.1"
msgid ""
"No ce, āvuso, bhikkhu paracittapariyāyakusalo hoti, atha ‘"
"sacittapariyāyakusalo bhavissāmī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"If a mendicant isn’t skilled in the ways of another’s mind, then they should "
"train themselves: ‘I will be skilled in the ways of my own mind.’"

msgctxt "an10.55:6.2"
msgid "evañhi vo, āvuso, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.104"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an10.55:7.1"
msgid "Kathañcāvuso, bhikkhu sacittapariyāyakusalo hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant skilled in the ways of their own mind?"

msgctxt "an10.55:7.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, itthī vā puriso vā daharo yuvā maṇḍanakajātiko ādāse vā "
"parisuddhe pariyodāte acche vā udapatte sakaṃ mukhanimittaṃ paccavekkhamāno "
"sace tattha passati rajaṃ vā aṅgaṇaṃ vā, tasseva rajassa vā aṅgaṇassa vā "
"pahānāya vāyamati."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a woman or man who was young, youthful, and fond of "
"adornments, and they check their own reflection in a clean bright mirror or "
"a clear bowl of water. If they see any dirt or blemish there, they’d try to "
"remove it."

msgctxt "an10.55:7.3"
msgid ""
"No ce tattha passati rajaṃ vā aṅgaṇaṃ vā, tenevattamano hoti "
"paripuṇṇasaṅkappo:"
msgstr ""
"But if they don’t see any dirt or blemish there, they’re happy with that, as "
"they’ve got all they wished for:"

msgctxt "an10.55:7.4"
msgid "‘lābhā vata me, parisuddhaṃ vata me’ti."
msgstr "‘How fortunate that I’m clean!’"

msgctxt "an10.55:7.5"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, āvuso, bhikkhuno paccavekkhaṇā bahukārā hoti kusalesu dhammesu:"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, checking is very helpful for a mendicant’s skillful "
"qualities."

msgctxt "an10.55:7.6"
msgid ""
"‘anabhijjhālu nu kho bahulaṃ viharāmi, saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu "
"no, abyāpannacitto nu kho bahulaṃ viharāmi, saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo "
"udāhu no, vigatathinamiddho nu kho bahulaṃ viharāmi, saṃvijjati nu kho me "
"eso dhammo udāhu no, anuddhato nu kho bahulaṃ viharāmi, saṃvijjati nu kho me "
"eso dhammo udāhu no, tiṇṇavicikiccho nu kho bahulaṃ viharāmi, saṃvijjati nu "
"kho me eso dhammo udāhu no, akkodhano nu kho bahulaṃ viharāmi, saṃvijjati nu "
"kho me eso dhammo udāhu no, asaṅkiliṭṭhacitto nu kho bahulaṃ viharāmi, "
"saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no, lābhī nu khomhi ajjhattaṃ "
"dhammapāmojjassa, saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no, lābhī nu khomhi "
"ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu no, lābhī nu "
"khomhi adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, saṃvijjati nu kho me eso dhammo udāhu "
"no’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Is contentment often found in me or not? Is kind-heartedness often found in "
"me or not? Is freedom from dullness and drowsiness often found in me or not? "
"Is calm often found in me or not? Is confidence often found in me or not? Is "
"love often found in me or not? Is purity of mind often found in me or not? "
"Is internal joy with the teaching found in me or not? Is internal serenity "
"of heart found in me or not? Is the higher wisdom of discernment of "
"principles found in me or not?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an10.55:8.1"
msgid ""
"Sace pana, āvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno sabbepime kusale dhamme attani na "
"samanupassati, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā sabbesaṃyeva imesaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"paṭilābhāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca appaṭivānī ca "
"sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a checking mendicant doesn’t see any of these skillful qualities in "
"themselves. In order to get them they should apply outstanding enthusiasm, "
"effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, mindfulness, and situational awareness."

msgctxt "an10.55:8.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, ādittacelo vā ādittasīso vā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose your clothes or head were on fire. In order to extinguish it, you’d "
"apply outstanding enthusiasm, effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, "
"mindfulness, and situational awareness."

msgctxt "an10.55:8.3"
msgid ""
"Tasseva celassa vā sīsassa vā nibbāpanāya adhimattaṃ chandañca vāyāmañca "
"ussāhañca ussoḷhiñca appaṭivāniñca satiñca sampajaññañca kareyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.55:8.4"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, tena bhikkhunā sabbesaṃyeva kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"paṭilābhāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca appaṭivānī ca "
"sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, they should apply outstanding enthusiasm to get those "
"skillful qualities …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.105"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an10.55:9.1"
msgid ""
"Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno ekacce kusale dhamme attani "
"samanupassati, ekacce kusale dhamme attani na samanupassati, tenāvuso, "
"bhikkhunā ye kusale dhamme attani samanupassati tesu kusalesu dhammesu "
"patiṭṭhāya, ye kusale dhamme attani na samanupassati tesaṃ kusalānaṃ "
"dhammānaṃ paṭilābhāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho ca ussoḷhī ca "
"appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a checking mendicant sees some of these skillful qualities in "
"themselves, but doesn’t see others. Grounded on the skillful qualities they "
"see, they should apply outstanding enthusiasm, effort, zeal, vigor, "
"perseverance, mindfulness, and situational awareness in order to get the "
"skillful qualities they don’t see."

msgctxt "an10.55:9.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso, ādittacelo vā ādittasīso vā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose your clothes or head were on fire. In order to extinguish it, you’d "
"apply outstanding enthusiasm, effort, zeal, vigor, perseverance, "
"mindfulness, and situational awareness."

msgctxt "an10.55:9.3"
msgid ""
"Tasseva celassa vā sīsassa vā nibbāpanāya adhimattaṃ chandañca vāyāmañca "
"ussāhañca ussoḷhiñca appaṭivāniñca satiñca sampajaññañca kareyya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an10.55:9.4"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, āvuso, tena bhikkhunā ye kusale dhamme attani samanupassati "
"tesu kusalesu dhammesu patiṭṭhāya, ye kusale dhamme attani na samanupassati "
"tesaṃ kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭilābhāya adhimatto chando ca vāyāmo ca ussāho "
"ca ussoḷhī ca appaṭivānī ca sati ca sampajaññañca karaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, grounded on the skillful qualities they see, they should "
"apply outstanding enthusiasm to get those skillful qualities they don’t see."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an10.55:10.1"
msgid ""
"Sace panāvuso, bhikkhu paccavekkhamāno sabbepime kusale dhamme attani "
"samanupassati, tenāvuso, bhikkhunā sabbesveva imesu kusalesu dhammesu "
"patiṭṭhāya uttari āsavānaṃ khayāya yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr ""
"But suppose a checking mendicant sees all of these skillful qualities in "
"themselves. Grounded on all these skillful qualities they should practice "
"meditation further to end the defilements.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.55:10.2"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
